{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3494164,"name":"","username":"iparsons","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/i/65b543/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-01-27T23:24:51.235Z","cooked":"

Hi

We’re trying to implement object detection of algae and coral in Photonvision. We generated an rknn file for the model from this data set modified to output yolo8, using the Frog Force Google-hosted Jupyter notebook modified to output yolov8, but Photonvision also wants a labels file. Adding a random labels file from the data set just recognizes everything in the scene, and is obviously not the intended file. (This could also be because we set a very low epoch count as we were just testing if our output file would be accepted by Photonvision, however, we still believe that just selecting a random singular labels file is incorrect and it likely requires a different and longer concatenated file) How do we generate a labels file for the model?

Thanks in advance.

A labels file just has what the model should recognize as the objects. It’s easy enough to create a labels file, all you have to do is just create a text file with each object as a separate line.

algae
coral

This is really all that text file needs, as long as it is in the correct order, which is the same order it would be in the dataset you trained this on.

You have to follow their naming scheme. Also, make sure the model is quantized (if you are using that colab, it should already be quantized).

Names for the model should be like this:

coral-640-640-yolov8.rknn

Naming the txt should be like this:

coral-640-640-yolov8-labels.txt

Currently, I don’t think PV can read it if you name it as a yolov11 model, but if you name it as a yolov8, it works fine.
